Hey there! The incentive credit isn't available for use right away. To become eligible, your account must complete and pass business verification, accumulate over $5,000 in spend, and establish a relationship with an Account Manager who can request the ad credit functionality for you. If you have any questions or need further assistance, feel free to reach out!
so i have to spend $5000 even after if its been added to my account and shows on blling tab

in what increments does my billing threshold increase

The billing threshold increases in increments based on your ad spend and payment history. Initially, it starts at a lower amount and gradually increases as you continue to run ads and make payments successfully. If you have specific questions about your current threshold, feel free to reach out to adsupport@newsbreak.com for more details.

is pausing  campaign during the learning phase really bad?

Yes, pausing a campaign during the learning phase can disrupt the system's ability to gather performance signals and optimize effectively. It's best to let the campaign run without interruptions during this phase to ensure it stabilizes and performs well. For more details, you can check out our article on maximizing conversions best practices.
what if i want to do it for a day then reactivate it

If you pause your campaign for a day and then reactivate it, it might still affect the learning phase. The system needs consistent data to optimize properly, so even a short pause can disrupt this process. It's recommended to avoid pausing during the learning phase if possible.
how long does the learning phase last
The learning phase typically lasts until your campaign achieves around 20-30 conversions. This can take a few days, depending on the volume of traffic and engagement your ad receives.
